 Version 0.1.5
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Released: 2011-11-01

* New Features:
 - Add a fake BRG profile from Kai-Uwe Behrmann (Richard Hughes)
 - Add another RBG profile for testing (Richard Hughes)
 - Tag the colorspace profiles with DATA_source=standard (Richard Hughes)
 - Tag the test profiles with DATA_source=test (Richard Hughes)
 - Tag the well-known colorspace profiles with STANDARD_space (Richard Hughes)

Version 0.1.4
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Released: 2011-04-08

* Bugfix:
 - Ensure all profiles have an embedded profile ID (Richard Hughes)

Version 0.1.3
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Released: 2011-01-11

* Bugfix:
 - Rename the Oyranos profiles to Oysonar to fix Kai-Uwe Behrmann's
   reported license violation (Richard Hughes)

Version 0.1.2
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Released: 2010-10-01

* New Features:
 - Add several other RGB colorspaces generated using Argyll and LCMS2
   using data from the SCARSE project (Richard Hughes)
 - Add the Yamma abstract profiles (Richard Hughes)
 - Add two further gray profiles from the Oyranos project (Richard Hughes)

Version 0.1.1
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Released: 2010-04-06

* New Features:
 - Add the Public Domain Fogra27L CMYK Coated Press ICC profile (Richard Hughes)
 - Add some profiles from Oyranos with a zlib licence (Richard Hughes)

Version 0.1.0
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Released: 2009-12-09

* New Features:
 - First release!
 - Add the free Argyll profiles that are in the public domain (Richard Hughes)

* Bugfix:
 - Don't install README and LICENSE in /usr/share/color (Richard Hughes)
 - Require color-filesystem on Fedora (Richard Hughes)

